	</div>
</div>Because it doesn't matter?  <br />
Think about it this way, the file system (folders etc) you see, doesn't necessarily correspond in any meaningful way to the hard drive geometry.  Just because the files sit next to each other in a folder, doesn't mean they'll be close to each other on the physical disk platter.  <br />
<br />
<br />
